“If you try to look at it, Basil, on my word of honour I will never speak to you again
as long as I live. I am quite serious. I don’t offer any explanation, and you are not to ask
for any. But, remember, if you touch this screen, everything is over between us.”
Hallward was thunderstruck. He looked at Dorian Gray in absolute amazement. He
had never seen him like this before. The lad was actually pallid with rage. His hands
were clenched, and the pupils of his eyes were like disks of blue fire. He was trembling
all over.
“Dorian!”
“Don’t speak!”
